    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the research and the plan:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` subcommand\n\n### What I found\n\n- **`CacheBucket::iter()`** yields 10 buckets: Wheels, SourceDistributions, FlatIndex, Git, Interpreter, Simple, Archive, Builds, Environments, Binaries — each with a `Display` impl returning versioned names like `\"wheels-v6\"`, `\"sdists-v9\"`, etc.\n- **`cache_size.rs`** is the direct model: it uses `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` for disk measurement and `human_readable_bytes()` for formatting. The only difference is `cache_size` has a `preview:` gating flag; `cache_stats` won't need that.\n- **`cache.bucket(bucket)`** returns a `PathBuf` for any given `CacheBucket`.\n\n### 4 changes needed\n\n1. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` enum + new `StatsArgs` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`).\n\n2. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new file)* — Loop over `CacheBucket::iter()`, measure each bucket with `DiskUsage`, print `{bucket}: {size}` per line, then `total: {total}` at the end.\n\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` alongside their `cache_size` counterparts.\n\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add one dispatch arm after `CacheCommand::Size`, calling `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)`.",
